        About this item

        • 16 SATA3.0 interfaces---This PCIE SATA card is equipped with 16 SATA 3.0 interfaces, supports simultaneous connection of 16 SATA hard drives, with a transmission speed of up to 6Gbps, and can add 16 SATA 3.0 6Gbps devices to your computer.
        • 256T expansion: The interface expands an additional 256TB, providing a massive database for your workstation or computer equipment.
        • Product chip---use ASMedia ASM1064+JMB5XX chip to enhance heat dissipation, long-lasting high temperature resistance, and more stable operation.
        • Support interface: PCI Express X1 slot, support PCI-E X4/ X8/ X16 at the same time. Please check if there is at least one PCIE X1 slot on the motherboard of the PC or server.
        • Support system: compatible with WIN 8/ WIN 10/ Linux/ MAC OS.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        • Chris
          5.0 out of 5 stars Great product - Can't boot into Windows? Here's the solution.
          Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2022
          Verified Purchase
          BEYIMEI PCIE SATA Card 16 Ports is what i bought. It's installed in a 1x slot on my motherboard.

          First off, the drivers.

          The drivers are odd. I installed the drivers that came included BUT, that doesn't really work (sort of). Windows device manager will show missing drivers BUT it still works so i just ignore device manager.

          I contacted the seller about the driver situation but they just contacted me back with the same drivers. I will admit though i didn't bother installing the drivers they sent me but that's because it looked like it was exactly the same drivers.

          Besides that everything works fine.....except one issue i ran into but found out how to fix it

          10 and under SATA drives worked fine. But when i added 11 and 12 total drives...i could no longer boot into windows 11.

          (Yes this works with Windows 10 and 11)

          I drove myself crazy wondering why the heck i couldn't start Windows. I tested everything. I tested the SATA power and data cables... i tried all sorts of combinations to try to figure out how to fix it....

          AND THEN i realized, if i unplug 2 SATA drives giving me a total of 10 drives. Everything works fine.

          Then i started to wonder, do i need a bigger PSU? My PSU is 850watts.

          As i was about to give up, (with my 12 total drives connected) i booted into my BIOS. I turned "fast boot" OFF.

          I saved my BIOS settings, restarted the PC and Windows booted up as normal!!

          IT WORKS NOW!

          So if you buy this, device, turn FAST BOOT off! or at least make a note of this, in case you install enough drives one day and you can't boot into windows. THIS MAY BE THE SOLUTION!

          I found that fast boot off works just like fast boot on. It's fast. Not sure why but for my motherboard it starts fast.

          I also want to note that i bought this product many months ago. And it still works and works good. Speed is good. I only came to review this product now to share my discovery about the "FAST BOOT" situation and solution. For anyone else who runs into this problem. Now you know!
